# .dockerignore — REPO ROOT
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The game image builds with the repo root as the Docker context (so Next sees
# the pnpm-workspace.yaml / turbo.json workspace markers and emits the nested
# standalone layout — see apps/game/Dockerfile). Docker reads .dockerignore from
# the CONTEXT ROOT, so THIS file (not apps/game/.dockerignore) governs the build.
# Deploy from the repo root:  fly deploy . --config apps/game/fly.toml
#
# Keep the context lean & deterministic: nothing host-built is shipped in; the
# Prisma client and .next/standalone are produced FRESH inside the image so the
# build can't be poisoned by stale local state.

# VCS & CI meta
.git
.gitignore
.github

# Secrets — NEVER ship into the image (real values arrive via `fly secrets set`)
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Dependencies & build output (reinstalled / regenerated in-image)
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/out
**/dist
apps/game/src/generated/prisma

# Not part of the game image
chain
spec
docs

# Tests & tooling not needed to build or run the server
tests
playwright*.config.*
**/__tests__
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts
**/*.spec.tsx
**/vitest.config.*
**/vitest.setup.*
apps/game/scripts/visual-debug

# Local env files & editor / OS cruft
.vscode
.idea
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log
**/coverage
